        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Portal Primitive\n\nThe portal is an addressed node that points at another graph or document. It can navigate there and, when configured, render a declared surface in place."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "portal-primitive-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What Portal Owns",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": 100,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-basic-primitives-portal"
        },
        "markdown": "## What portal does\n\nUse `portal` when a node should point at another graph or document by address.\n\nA portal combines:\n- target address\n- navigation behavior\n- optional surface selection\n\nThat makes it the primitive that turns declared surfaces into reusable in-graph windows."
      }
    },
